Reports unlabeled 'return' expressions inside inline lambda. Such expressions can be confusing because it might be unclear which scope belongs to 'return'. Change to return@â€¦ quick-fix can be used to amend the code automatically. Example: 'fun test(list: List<Int>) {
      list.forEach {
          // This return expression returns from the function test
          // One can change it to return@forEach to change the scope
          if (it == 10) return
      }
  }' After the quick-fix is applied: 'fun test(list: List<Int>) {
      list.forEach {
          if (it == 10) return@test
      }
  }'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports unlabeled `return` expressions inside inline lambda.

Such expressions can be confusing because it might be unclear which scope belongs to `return`.

**Change to return@...** quick-fix can be used to amend the code automatically.

Example:


      fun test(list: List<Int>) {
          list.forEach {
              // This return expression returns from the function test
              // One can change it to return@forEach to change the scope
              if (it == 10) return
          }
      }

After the quick-fix is applied:


      fun test(list: List<Int>) {
          list.forEach {
              if (it == 10) return@test
          }
      }

