Reports 'for' loops with a manually incremented index variable. 'for' loops with a manually incremented index variable can be simplified with the 'withIndex()' function. Use withIndex() instead of manual index increment quick-fix can be used to amend the code automatically. Example: 'fun foo(list: List<String>): Int? {
      var index = 0
      for (s in list) { <== can be simplified
          val x = s.length * index
          index++
          if (x > 0) return x
