Reports 'if-then' expressions that can be folded into safe-access ('?.') expressions. Example: 'fun bar(x: String) = ""

  fun foo(a: String?) {
     if (a != null) bar(a) else null
  }' The quick fix converts the 'if-then' expression into a safe-access ('?.') expression: 'fun bar(x: String) = ""

  fun foo(a: String?) {
     a?.let { bar(it) }
  }'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports `if-then` expressions that can be folded into safe-access (`?.`) expressions.

**Example:**


      fun bar(x: String) = ""

      fun foo(a: String?) {
         if (a != null) bar(a) else null
      }

The quick fix converts the `if-then` expression into a safe-access (`?.`) expression:


      fun bar(x: String) = ""

      fun foo(a: String?) {
         a?.let { bar(it) }
      }

